In a bid to further educate and enlighten the members of the banking community and other stakeholders in the economy on the current banking reforms, Mr. Godwin Emefiele, CON, FCIB, Governor, Central Bank of Nigeria will deliver a Keynote Address on the state of the Banking Industry and the economy. The Address is expected to give perspectives on the focus of the regulatory authorities on banking and the Nigerian economy in 2018 and beyond.  In a press/invitation statement by mrs Chinwe Henry Edero, Head, Corporate Communications & External Relations of the institute disclosed that Mr. Emefiele’s Address which will be presented at the 2017 Annual Bankers Dinner on Friday, November 10, 2017 at Harbour Point, 4 Wilmot Point Road, Off Ahmadu Bello Way, Victoria Island, Lagos, at 6.00 p.m. prompt, is in line with the tradition of the Dinner where the CBN Governor is the Special Guest of Honour.  The British Deputy High Commissioner, Ms. Laure Beaufils  is expected to be the Guest of Honour and will present the Toast of the Federal Republic.  The Dinner which is organized by the Chartered Institute of Bankers of Nigeria will attract top dignitaries from the banking and finance industries, the business community, members of the diplomatic corps and top government functionaries.  Prof. Segun Ajibola, FCIB, President/Chairman of Council, CIBN, will be the Chairman while Mr. Seye Awojobi, FCIB, Registrar/CE will be the Chief Host of the event.   